1
00:00:50,050 --> 00:00:51,051
[sighs]

2
00:00:51,135 --> 00:00:53,637
[anxious music playing]

3
00:01:11,155 --> 00:01:12,156
[chuckles]

4
00:01:13,532 --> 00:01:15,117
[knock on door]

5
00:01:26,629 --> 00:01:27,880
[music stops]

6
00:01:27,963 --> 00:01:29,507
Would you like to see the menu, sir?

7
00:01:30,382 --> 00:01:33,135
Ah, uh… [chuckles] …yeah, thanks.

8
00:01:36,722 --> 00:01:37,973
-Good work, everyone!
-[clamoring]

9
00:01:38,057 --> 00:01:40,017
Great session, thank you.
Nice to see you all!

10
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:43,062
-Have a great week, I'll see you soon!
-[student] Wanna grab a coffee?

11
00:01:43,145 --> 00:01:44,563
[sighs]

12
00:01:46,607 --> 00:01:49,568
I wonder how it's going. Funny,
my sister's the one on a blind date,

13
00:01:49,652 --> 00:01:51,987
-so why do I have butterflies?
-[chuckles]

14
00:01:52,071 --> 00:01:54,198
I hope it goes well, brother-in-law.
Don't you?

15
00:01:54,281 --> 00:01:55,449
Sure.

16
00:01:56,450 --> 00:01:58,536
Hey, your sister is
strong mentally, right?

17
00:01:58,619 --> 00:01:59,620
Any heart issues?

18
00:01:59,703 --> 00:02:01,580
The Ukraine war, for example,

19
00:02:01,664 --> 00:02:03,123
the Israel-Palestine conflict.

20
00:02:03,207 --> 00:02:06,377
It's frightening that the world is
becoming desensitized to these wars.

21
00:02:06,460 --> 00:02:09,713
No one seems to realize that the world
order which was once very stable,

22
00:02:09,797 --> 00:02:11,340
is now coming apart.

23
00:02:11,423 --> 00:02:13,968
And that's the reason
there have been so many

24
00:02:14,051 --> 00:02:15,803
-World War III predictions.
-Sorry, I just…

25
00:02:16,303 --> 00:02:18,848
I was under the impression
you're a flight attendant,

26
00:02:18,931 --> 00:02:21,350
but… [scoffs] …you seem
really interested in world politics.

27
00:02:21,433 --> 00:02:22,643
Flight attendant?

28
00:02:24,436 --> 00:02:25,729
A stewardess?

29
00:02:27,606 --> 00:02:30,317
[inhales sharply] Oh, wait.
Aren't you a detective?

30
00:02:30,401 --> 00:02:32,278
A detective?

31
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:35,072
No. No, I'm a civil servant.

32
00:02:35,155 --> 00:02:36,866
-I work at City Hall.
-Civil…

33
00:02:36,949 --> 00:02:39,118
Aren't you a flight attendant
with Asia Airlines?

34
00:02:39,201 --> 00:02:40,953
-You think that I…
-[knock on door]

35
00:02:43,747 --> 00:02:45,749
[comedic music playing]

36
00:02:55,050 --> 00:02:56,051
[music stops]

37
00:02:57,094 --> 00:02:58,512
God. [chuckles]

38
00:02:58,596 --> 00:03:01,473
I've got no sympathy for women
who show up late to a date.

39
00:03:01,557 --> 00:03:02,933
Seriously!

40
00:03:03,017 --> 00:03:04,351
She calls herself a journalist.

41
00:03:04,435 --> 00:03:06,937
Since when are journalists
so frickin' late?

42
00:03:07,021 --> 00:03:09,690
You wanna leave a good first impression
on a blind date.

43
00:03:09,773 --> 00:03:11,942
[sighs] Look at the clock. This is insane!

44
00:03:12,026 --> 00:03:14,111
Well, we've found out
why the girl's single.

45
00:03:14,987 --> 00:03:16,530
And I didn't get any contact info.

46
00:03:16,614 --> 00:03:18,824
So, what am I supposed to do here?

47
00:03:18,908 --> 00:03:20,701
Seon-u, what the hell? Should I just go?

48
00:03:22,244 --> 00:03:23,245
Ah, shit!

49
00:03:24,413 --> 00:03:26,749
[Jeong-sin] Can you let that guy know
I'm running late because of traffic?

50
00:03:26,832 --> 00:03:29,585
-Wait, you haven't met him yet?
-This is why I should've gotten his cell.

51
00:03:29,668 --> 00:03:32,421
I ended up in a room with some man
who works at City Hall.

52
00:03:32,504 --> 00:03:33,797
Ugh, later!

53
00:03:33,881 --> 00:03:35,549
-Not helping one bit.
-[phone beeps]

54
00:03:36,425 --> 00:03:38,344
[sighs] Well, that started off wrong.

55
00:03:39,803 --> 00:03:41,805
What is it? So, they haven't even met yet?

56
00:03:41,889 --> 00:03:45,351
No, she told me she got stuck in traffic
and she's gonna be like half an hour late.

57
00:03:45,434 --> 00:03:47,269
-Can you call your brother?
-Sure.

58
00:03:50,814 --> 00:03:52,650
You said she might be surprised
when she meets him.

59
00:03:52,733 --> 00:03:53,984
What does that mean?

60
00:03:54,068 --> 00:03:55,361
Oh, that.

61
00:03:55,444 --> 00:03:58,322
Uh, yeah, there's this one thing
about my brother.

62
00:03:58,405 --> 00:03:59,823
Huh?

63
00:03:59,907 --> 00:04:00,908
[laughs]

64
00:04:00,991 --> 00:04:03,994
Seriously, that's the lamest
excuse possible.

65
00:04:04,078 --> 00:04:06,872
Wow, the traffic is just so terrible.

66
00:04:07,456 --> 00:04:10,501
Wow, I gotta give it to her.
That's ruthless.

67
00:04:10,584 --> 00:04:12,211
[scoffs] Seriously.

68
00:04:13,629 --> 00:04:14,630
[breathes deeply]

69
00:04:17,967 --> 00:04:18,968
Yeah?

70
00:04:22,972 --> 00:04:23,973
Oh.

71
00:04:24,056 --> 00:04:26,558
[enchanting music playing]

72
00:04:29,603 --> 00:04:30,604
Uh…

73
00:04:36,151 --> 00:04:38,153
[heartbeat thumping]

74
00:04:49,415 --> 00:04:51,125
You? Uh.

75
00:04:51,208 --> 00:04:52,626
[music fades]

76
00:04:53,502 --> 00:04:55,796
Uh, what are you doing here?

77
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:58,716
Did I just walk into the wrong room again?

78
00:05:00,509 --> 00:05:02,344
I hear he looks a lot like my bro Pil-gu.

79
00:05:02,428 --> 00:05:04,388
Lim Hyeon-jun.

80
00:05:04,471 --> 00:05:08,308
-[echoing] Lim Hyeon-jun.
-[chuckles]

81
00:05:10,144 --> 00:05:11,145
Hello?

82
00:05:13,439 --> 00:05:15,107
You don't remember?

83
00:05:15,190 --> 00:05:17,401
[stammers] Remember?

84
00:05:20,988 --> 00:05:23,532
I think your face does look a little, uh…

85
00:05:25,409 --> 00:05:26,994
familiar. Do I know you?

86
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:31,540
Journalist. Hanguk University.

87
00:05:31,623 --> 00:05:34,668
[echoing] Journalist.

88
00:05:35,210 --> 00:05:37,171
[shouting, gasping]

89
00:05:39,965 --> 00:05:41,508
What the… [grunts]

90
00:05:42,468 --> 00:05:45,763
-[Seon-u] Are you all right?
-[chuckles] Okay, so…

91
00:05:45,846 --> 00:05:47,931
so, your brother's Lim Hyeon-jun?

92
00:05:48,515 --> 00:05:52,019
And so the man my sister's
on a date with is Kang Pil-gu?

93
00:05:52,102 --> 00:05:53,270
Kang Pil-gu from the show?

94
00:05:53,353 --> 00:05:56,106
See, I wasn't lying
about him being a detective.

95
00:05:56,607 --> 00:05:57,608
[chuckles]

96
00:06:01,445 --> 00:06:03,697
[gasps] Oh, no. This is not good.

97
00:06:04,448 --> 00:06:05,491
What? Why?

98
00:06:05,574 --> 00:06:09,203
God, isn't it such a small world?

99
00:06:09,286 --> 00:06:11,622
-Who would've thought, right?
-You're right.

100
00:06:12,623 --> 00:06:13,874
[knock on door]

101
00:06:20,047 --> 00:06:21,548
-So, are we ready to order?
-Yes.

102
00:06:21,632 --> 00:06:22,925
It's lunchtime anyhow.

103
00:06:23,008 --> 00:06:25,135
-So, I guess we'll take, uh… Yeah.
-Iced Americano, please.

104
00:06:25,219 --> 00:06:26,678
Same here, iced Americano please.

105
00:06:26,762 --> 00:06:28,055
[server] Right away, sir.

106
00:06:28,931 --> 00:06:30,641
Given the situation,

107
00:06:30,724 --> 00:06:33,227
I thought you didn't really want to
have lunch together.

108
00:06:33,310 --> 00:06:35,229
[scoffs] I appreciate you
picking up on that.

109
00:06:37,064 --> 00:06:38,565
[Hong-sin]
I've got this buddy in med school.

110
00:06:38,649 --> 00:06:40,567
His brother's a detective.
Might be a good match.

111
00:06:40,651 --> 00:06:43,695
-I was told you were a detective.
-Kang Pil-gu's a detective.

112
00:06:43,779 --> 00:06:45,197
And he's my alter ego. So…

113
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:46,365
[sighs]

114
00:06:46,448 --> 00:06:48,408
Are you gonna turn this
into an article too?

115
00:06:48,492 --> 00:06:50,369
"Myself and Actor Lim Hyeon-jun
on a Blind Date."

116
00:06:50,452 --> 00:06:52,621
I'm not petty enough
to write an article like that, all right?

117
00:06:52,704 --> 00:06:54,915
[scoffs] Oh, I don't know.

118
00:06:55,624 --> 00:06:57,876
'Cause I recall
you actually being so petty,

119
00:06:57,960 --> 00:07:00,379
that you dug through
my social media, because…

120
00:07:00,462 --> 00:07:02,673
you wanted to search my dating history.

121
00:07:05,175 --> 00:07:06,343
I was…

122
00:07:06,426 --> 00:07:08,220
blinded by revenge back then.

123
00:07:08,804 --> 00:07:11,431
[sighs] Well, thank you
for admitting that.

124
00:07:12,349 --> 00:07:15,936
Anyway, as I understand it
our brothers are friends.

125
00:07:16,019 --> 00:07:17,521
So, is your brother also in med school?

126
00:07:17,604 --> 00:07:20,440
No, my brother's a theater major.

127
00:07:22,234 --> 00:07:23,735
A theater major? Really?

128
00:07:24,570 --> 00:07:26,613
If my bro Pil-gu finds out where we met,

129
00:07:26,697 --> 00:07:28,240
he's definitely gonna lose it.

130
00:07:28,323 --> 00:07:29,741
It's a cruel world, isn't it?

131
00:07:30,951 --> 00:07:31,952
[both sigh]

132
00:07:32,035 --> 00:07:34,830
Brother's in theater.
Is that somehow a problem for you?

133
00:07:36,039 --> 00:07:37,040
Not at all.

134
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:40,377
That doesn't mean I like him
hanging out with my little brother.

135
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:42,671
-It's not his fault.
-You don't like your med-student

136
00:07:42,754 --> 00:07:44,548
hanging around a wild child
like my brother.

137
00:07:44,631 --> 00:07:45,883
I suppose you must feel insecure

138
00:07:45,966 --> 00:07:48,218
because your brother
doesn't do well in school.

139
00:07:48,302 --> 00:07:49,803
-[scoffs]
-[chuckles]

140
00:07:51,054 --> 00:07:54,266
Whatever, I'm not sure if it's fate
which brought us together here.

141
00:07:54,349 --> 00:07:56,935
-But it's pretty weird.
-[scoffs] Did you say fate?

142
00:07:57,019 --> 00:07:59,146
So, I guess it's best
if we just go our separate ways?

143
00:07:59,229 --> 00:08:00,689
You got that right.

144
00:08:02,774 --> 00:08:03,984
Wait, I'm going first.

145
00:08:07,279 --> 00:08:09,239
[thunder rumbles]

146
00:08:09,323 --> 00:08:11,033
EPISODE 4

147
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:23,837
[sighs]

148
00:08:25,339 --> 00:08:26,715
[grunts, groans]

149
00:08:28,133 --> 00:08:30,177
[exhales deeply]

150
00:08:31,261 --> 00:08:32,262
[sighs heavily]

151
00:08:44,775 --> 00:08:47,194
Where's she going?
She doesn't even have an umbrella?

152
00:08:47,778 --> 00:08:49,863
I don't care. Whatever, do your thing.

153
00:08:54,451 --> 00:08:56,745
[comedic music playing]

154
00:09:03,669 --> 00:09:05,754
Oh, no. She's getting soaked.

155
00:09:05,837 --> 00:09:08,257
Just look at that new dress,
it's completely wet.

156
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:11,593
There are taxis all around.
Why doesn't she get a taxi? Come on.

157
00:09:16,765 --> 00:09:17,891
Huh?

158
00:09:19,393 --> 00:09:20,435
Oh, yeah. Good idea.

159
00:09:20,519 --> 00:09:22,980
Go ahead. Yeah, get an umbrella.

160
00:09:26,775 --> 00:09:27,859
PRICE 19,900 WON

161
00:09:36,493 --> 00:09:37,953
[music continues]

162
00:09:39,871 --> 00:09:41,206
Come on, just get it.

163
00:09:41,290 --> 00:09:44,001
Just buy a frickin' umbrella.
They're so cheap here.

164
00:09:49,965 --> 00:09:52,968
No, she shouldn't be running around
like that after the surgery!

165
00:09:53,051 --> 00:09:54,594
Her stomach must be hurting.

166
00:09:55,721 --> 00:09:56,722
[sighs]

167
00:09:57,597 --> 00:09:59,766
Okay then, I'll give her a ride.

168
00:10:04,104 --> 00:10:05,105
[music stops]

169
00:10:07,149 --> 00:10:10,277
-Dodged a bullet.
-[tender music playing]

170
00:10:12,321 --> 00:10:13,655
[sighs]

171
00:10:52,027 --> 00:10:54,237
-[door slams]
-[music fades]

172
00:10:54,321 --> 00:10:55,364
[Hong-sin] Hey, there.

173
00:10:57,074 --> 00:10:58,408
-Whoa, easy!
-What did you say?

174
00:10:58,492 --> 00:11:00,202
-I can trust you completely?
-Hey, calm down!

175
00:11:00,285 --> 00:11:01,703
Seriously, calm down, sis.

176
00:11:01,787 --> 00:11:04,247
I swear, I had no idea
his brother was Pil-gu.

177
00:11:04,748 --> 00:11:07,000
He said if you swap contact info
or photos beforehand,

178
00:11:07,084 --> 00:11:08,752
it's easy to find
each other's social media.

179
00:11:08,835 --> 00:11:10,379
And it takes away from the excitement.

180
00:11:10,462 --> 00:11:13,048
I didn't know he was trying to hide
his brother's identity.

181
00:11:13,131 --> 00:11:14,299
[huffs]

182
00:11:17,427 --> 00:11:18,637
[sighs]

183
00:11:28,563 --> 00:11:30,232
You wanna tell me how the date went?

184
00:11:30,732 --> 00:11:32,692
-How do you think, genius?
-[chuckles]

185
00:11:32,776 --> 00:11:35,529
Well, you walked in looking all beautiful
and Pil-gu fell for you

186
00:11:35,612 --> 00:11:37,197
-the moment he laid eyes on you.
-What?

187
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:42,035
I mean, you wrote
a nice article about him.

188
00:11:42,119 --> 00:11:43,620
Not to mention,
the man literally saved you.

189
00:11:43,703 --> 00:11:45,539
-[scoffs]
-I thought you two would really hit off,

190
00:11:45,622 --> 00:11:46,998
you know?

191
00:11:47,082 --> 00:11:48,458
Why are you all wet?

192
00:11:48,542 --> 00:11:50,669
You mean to tell me
he didn't offer you a ride?

193
00:11:50,752 --> 00:11:54,256
[scoffs] And why the hell
would he do that?

194
00:11:56,216 --> 00:11:57,384
Such a shame.

195
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:00,262
I could've been Pil-gu's brother-in-law.

196
00:12:00,345 --> 00:12:01,847
Okay, stop! [scoffs]

197
00:12:01,930 --> 00:12:03,598
You know what?
I'll show you brother-in-law.

198
00:12:03,682 --> 00:12:04,975
-Come here, you little jerk!
-Stop it!

199
00:12:05,058 --> 00:12:07,018
Why would you hit me?
I'm just trying to help!

200
00:12:08,812 --> 00:12:12,232
[chuckles] I wasn't aware that
you already knew my friend's sister.

201
00:12:12,315 --> 00:12:14,151
Oh, no, we're not discussing that.

202
00:12:14,234 --> 00:12:17,070
Let's talk about
your buddy Hong-sin instead.

203
00:12:17,154 --> 00:12:18,405
Where'd you meet that kid?

204
00:12:18,488 --> 00:12:21,116
-Uh, why?
-Just tell me. Answer the question!

205
00:12:22,534 --> 00:12:24,661
-Why ask, when you already know?
-[scoffs]

206
00:12:24,744 --> 00:12:26,955
So it's true.
You really wanna be an actor?

207
00:12:28,039 --> 00:12:30,083
Have you gone crazy, huh?

208
00:12:30,584 --> 00:12:33,211
I didn't wanna say this
because I feel bad for taking credit.

209
00:12:33,295 --> 00:12:36,506
However, I had to pick up delivery jobs
while I worked at the print shop,

210
00:12:36,590 --> 00:12:39,676
just so you, my smart little brother,
wouldn't miss out on medical school

211
00:12:39,759 --> 00:12:41,136
because we couldn't afford it.

212
00:12:41,219 --> 00:12:42,804
So I pushed myself to keep you going.

213
00:12:42,888 --> 00:12:45,682
-Did you know that?
-I did. Yeah.

214
00:12:47,309 --> 00:12:49,644
I know you paid for those lessons
even though we were poor,

215
00:12:50,145 --> 00:12:53,440
and that you bought me nice clothes so
I wouldn't feel small around my friends.

216
00:12:53,523 --> 00:12:55,275
I'm grateful for you
stepping up like that.

217
00:12:55,775 --> 00:12:57,277
I know it was difficult.

218
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:58,820
So you knew about that?

219
00:12:59,654 --> 00:13:01,656
Apparently, it didn't stop you
from doing this.

220
00:13:01,740 --> 00:13:03,200
What about Mom?

221
00:13:03,283 --> 00:13:04,284
Sorry for lying.

222
00:13:04,367 --> 00:13:06,453
I just… I really wanna be an actor.

223
00:13:06,536 --> 00:13:07,537
[sighs]

224
00:13:08,622 --> 00:13:10,207
You think it's easy, right?
Because I do it.

225
00:13:10,290 --> 00:13:12,584
Do you even know the amount of people
who wanna be actors

226
00:13:12,667 --> 00:13:15,170
because they have a famous relative,
and then fail?

227
00:13:15,253 --> 00:13:17,047
I don't intend to use your name
to get ahead.

228
00:13:17,130 --> 00:13:20,091
And our relationship
is much better kept hidden.

229
00:13:21,927 --> 00:13:23,637
Being half-brothers
is nothing to brag about.

230
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:26,348
[stammers]

231
00:13:26,932 --> 00:13:27,974
Hey, come back!

232
00:13:29,684 --> 00:13:30,977
Lim Seon-u!

233
00:13:32,270 --> 00:13:33,772
[colleague] See you guys in about an hour.

234
00:13:33,855 --> 00:13:35,232
SPORTS EUNSEONG

235
00:13:35,315 --> 00:13:37,734
-[chattering]
-If it's about work, don't text me.

236
00:13:39,069 --> 00:13:40,570
Hey, are you not having lunch?

237
00:13:40,654 --> 00:13:42,072
Uh, no. I'm good.

238
00:13:42,155 --> 00:13:43,156
[Seong-min] All right.

239
00:13:44,866 --> 00:13:46,076
Wait up, guys.

240
00:13:47,369 --> 00:13:49,371
-[enchanting music plays]
-[chuckles]

241
00:13:54,209 --> 00:13:56,378
[heartbeat thumps]

242
00:14:31,162 --> 00:14:32,163
[sighs]

243
00:15:04,487 --> 00:15:07,991
[heartbeat thumping]

244
00:15:15,624 --> 00:15:16,625
Hey, man.

245
00:15:16,708 --> 00:15:19,002
Have you heard back
from that US agency or what?

246
00:15:19,085 --> 00:15:20,253
[scoffs]

247
00:15:20,337 --> 00:15:23,256
They're so damn slow.
They haven't read my e-mail.

248
00:15:23,340 --> 00:15:26,593
[sighs heavily] Those big shots.
That's what they do, am I right?

249
00:15:26,676 --> 00:15:28,178
Oh, man. Hey, did you…

250
00:15:28,261 --> 00:15:30,138
did you read the article Ms. Wi wrote?

251
