741
00:41:17,434 --> 00:41:18,977
[Hyeon-jun]
Do you really work as a journalist?

742
00:41:19,060 --> 00:41:20,145
-It's a fake card!
-Huh?

743
00:41:20,228 --> 00:41:22,272
You know what happens
if you impersonate a journalist?

744
00:41:22,355 --> 00:41:23,607
Huh?

745
00:41:23,690 --> 00:41:24,816
No way.

746
00:41:25,358 --> 00:41:27,402
Zero chance this one's a journalist.

747
00:41:27,485 --> 00:41:28,528
But…

748
00:41:30,488 --> 00:41:33,283
Did you believe I was one
of the escorts working there?

749
00:41:33,366 --> 00:41:35,243
[scoffs] Okay, come on.

750
00:41:35,327 --> 00:41:38,246
I'm pretty sure you weren't there
for some undercover activity

751
00:41:38,330 --> 00:41:40,415
the way you were dressed. [scoffs]

752
00:41:40,957 --> 00:41:41,958
[sighs]

753
00:41:46,963 --> 00:41:48,924
You sure I wasn't doing that?

754
00:41:51,468 --> 00:41:52,469
[door opens]

755
00:41:54,429 --> 00:41:56,056
[sighs]

756
00:41:57,224 --> 00:42:00,685
I'm the one who should be angry.
I don't understand why she acts like that.

757
00:42:05,690 --> 00:42:06,691
[pants]

758
00:42:08,401 --> 00:42:09,819
Ah, shit!

759
00:42:13,198 --> 00:42:14,574
I'm exhausted.

760
00:42:20,497 --> 00:42:21,581
[groans]

761
00:42:23,291 --> 00:42:25,961
I don't think that's something to hide.

762
00:42:26,044 --> 00:42:27,963
Do you wanna hide your mother that much?

763
00:42:29,130 --> 00:42:31,967
[groans] That was some day.

764
00:42:35,887 --> 00:42:37,264
Let's see.

765
00:42:37,931 --> 00:42:38,932
[clicks tongue]

766
00:42:39,557 --> 00:42:41,226
[exclaims]

767
00:42:41,309 --> 00:42:44,312
Nice! They already got back to me, huh?

768
00:42:51,361 --> 00:42:54,072
MAYBE NEXT TIME

769
00:42:54,155 --> 00:42:55,198
[sighs]

770
00:42:55,782 --> 00:42:57,284
[smacks lips] Well, all right.

771
00:42:58,076 --> 00:43:00,495
You can't win every time,
that's not realistic.

772
00:43:00,578 --> 00:43:01,830
Here we go.

773
00:43:02,706 --> 00:43:03,707
YOU DID NOT GET THE ROLE

774
00:43:04,708 --> 00:43:05,709
[sighs]

775
00:43:06,626 --> 00:43:07,627
[clicks tongue]

776
00:43:08,253 --> 00:43:09,587
[sighs]

777
00:43:09,671 --> 00:43:11,464
-[phone buzzes]
-Oh, boy.

778
00:43:12,215 --> 00:43:13,300
Geez.

779
00:43:14,968 --> 00:43:17,178
It's me, Se-na. Are you feeling better?

780
00:43:18,221 --> 00:43:19,222
[sighs]

781
00:43:19,306 --> 00:43:20,890
IT'S ME, SE-NA.
ARE YOU FEELING BETTER NOW?

782
00:43:24,853 --> 00:43:25,854
[phone clatters]

783
00:43:26,980 --> 00:43:28,315
[sighs]

784
00:43:28,398 --> 00:43:30,400
[calm music playing]

785
00:43:32,902 --> 00:43:34,446
[sighs]

786
00:43:34,529 --> 00:43:36,740
[Jeong-sin] It's 2025, isn't it?

787
00:43:36,823 --> 00:43:40,035
Voluntary single motherhood
and same-sex marriage are supported now,

788
00:43:40,118 --> 00:43:42,203
and people are more relaxed about it all.

789
00:43:42,287 --> 00:43:45,498
Honestly, I think it's better
to be up front with these kinds of things.

790
00:43:47,959 --> 00:43:49,002
[sighs]

791
00:43:51,546 --> 00:43:52,714
"RETIRED ACTRESS SEONG AE-SUK

792
00:43:52,797 --> 00:43:54,382
BACK IN THE SPOTLIGHT,
THANKS TO HER SON"

793
00:43:54,466 --> 00:43:56,760
[Jeong-sin]
I don't think that's something to hide.

794
00:43:56,843 --> 00:43:58,928
Do you wanna hide your mother that much?

795
00:43:59,679 --> 00:44:01,139
[sighs]

796
00:44:04,142 --> 00:44:06,227
[exhales deeply]

797
00:44:07,020 --> 00:44:08,480
[keypad beeping]

798
00:44:08,563 --> 00:44:10,190
-[door opens]
-[lock beeps]

799
00:44:11,608 --> 00:44:12,692
[door closes]

800
00:44:12,776 --> 00:44:14,069
[Ae-suk] Hey, Jun!

801
00:44:14,152 --> 00:44:15,570
Jun!

802
00:44:19,532 --> 00:44:20,909
[grunts]

803
00:44:23,119 --> 00:44:24,245
[chuckles]

804
00:44:24,329 --> 00:44:26,331
-Jun, hi!
-Oh, hi.

805
00:44:29,584 --> 00:44:30,877
[sighs]

806
00:44:30,960 --> 00:44:32,837
It's really early. What's going on?

807
00:44:32,921 --> 00:44:34,255
I'm exhausted.

808
00:44:34,339 --> 00:44:36,674
I feel like a criminal running
from the law suddenly.

809
00:44:36,758 --> 00:44:38,718
Uh, so what's all that, hmm?

810
00:44:39,219 --> 00:44:42,013
I'll be in the US
until everything's settled down.

811
00:44:42,097 --> 00:44:45,141
Everyone's saying I'm a roadblock
to your future, it's gotten outta control.

812
00:44:45,225 --> 00:44:46,226
-What did I ever do?
-[sighs]

813
00:44:46,309 --> 00:44:48,186
Ugh, whatever. Don't go.

814
00:44:48,269 --> 00:44:50,563
The whole planet knows now,
you might as well stay in Korea.

815
00:44:50,647 --> 00:44:52,065
Geez.

816
00:44:52,899 --> 00:44:54,234
All right.

817
00:44:54,317 --> 00:44:57,237
I'll listen to what you say.
If you want me to stay, I will.

818
00:44:57,320 --> 00:44:58,321
[clicks tongue, sighs]

819
00:44:58,405 --> 00:45:00,448
By the way, that reporter
who wrote about me,

820
00:45:00,532 --> 00:45:02,450
what does she have against you?

821
00:45:02,534 --> 00:45:03,952
Seon-u said she also did that thing

822
00:45:04,035 --> 00:45:06,538
about your Liberation Day sushi
and the romance thing as well…

823
00:45:06,621 --> 00:45:09,582
Ugh, cut, cut, cut, cut, cut, cut.
Don't get carried away.

824
00:45:09,666 --> 00:45:12,919
Reporters aren't obligated to
only write nice things about me though.

825
00:45:13,002 --> 00:45:16,089
When you were in the hospital she actually
wrote a really nice article about you.

826
00:45:18,591 --> 00:45:21,010
[exhales sharply] She should stay
out of my way, I can tell you that.

827
00:45:21,094 --> 00:45:22,637
Or she might regret it.

828
00:45:22,720 --> 00:45:26,474
Listen, you can stop hiding now,
thanks to that article.

829
00:45:27,058 --> 00:45:29,978
If anything, shouldn't you be grateful
for what she did?

830
00:45:30,061 --> 00:45:33,565
Excuse me, are you siding
with that nasty reporter now?

831
00:45:33,648 --> 00:45:35,316
Why would I ever side with her?

832
00:45:38,528 --> 00:45:40,029
Wait, isn't that your suitcase?

833
00:45:40,530 --> 00:45:41,865
Oh, that?

834
00:45:41,948 --> 00:45:43,992
-I came here to live with you.
-Sorry, what?

835
00:45:44,075 --> 00:45:45,702
-Mm-hmm.
-Why?

836
00:45:45,785 --> 00:45:48,288
You took too many of your sleeping pills
and ended up in the hospital.

837
00:45:48,371 --> 00:45:49,998
So we need someone to keep an eye on you.

838
00:45:50,081 --> 00:45:52,208
Come on. I'm a grown up.

839
00:45:52,292 --> 00:45:53,626
He's staying.

840
00:45:53,710 --> 00:45:55,879
Just let him stay with you
for 30 days or so.

841
00:45:55,962 --> 00:45:57,881
If something like that
ever happened again,

842
00:45:58,548 --> 00:46:00,300
I'll be on my way to an early grave.

843
00:46:01,092 --> 00:46:04,220
Hyeon-jun, chill out.
I'll just stay outta your way.

844
00:46:09,267 --> 00:46:10,351
Yeah, sure.

845
00:46:11,144 --> 00:46:12,562
Thirty days, that's it.

846
00:46:13,396 --> 00:46:15,899
You can have the room at the end.
Now go unpack, okay?

847
00:46:15,982 --> 00:46:17,358
-[Seon-u] Mm-hmm.
-[Hyeon-jun grunts]

848
00:46:22,489 --> 00:46:23,740
I have a question for you.

849
00:46:24,574 --> 00:46:26,117
Who's my father?

850
00:46:26,701 --> 00:46:28,786
-Your father's dead, you know that.
-Come on.

851
00:46:28,870 --> 00:46:30,580
I don't mean Seon-u's dad. Not my stepdad.

852
00:46:30,663 --> 00:46:33,374
My real biological dad.

853
00:46:34,959 --> 00:46:37,837
Ugh, your real dad died too.
I already told you that.

854
00:46:39,088 --> 00:46:42,342
Then what are the rumors of you having
a child with some rich business guy

855
00:46:42,425 --> 00:46:44,093
and then retiring, hmm?

856
00:46:44,802 --> 00:46:46,930
[grunts] If you were a rich man's kid,

857
00:46:47,013 --> 00:46:48,973
you think I would've
just let him go like that?

858
00:46:49,057 --> 00:46:52,018
You don't think I did everything I could
so you boys didn't have to struggle?

859
00:46:52,894 --> 00:46:55,939
[chuckling softly]

860
00:47:02,487 --> 00:47:04,489
[phone buzzing]

861
00:47:20,046 --> 00:47:21,923
[Hyeon-jun] Fine. Whatever.

862
00:47:22,632 --> 00:47:24,175
If you had any conscience whatsoever,

863
00:47:24,259 --> 00:47:26,970
then shouldn't you be apologizing
at the very least?

864
00:47:27,053 --> 00:47:29,055
-Ugh.
-[buzzing continues]

865
00:47:34,269 --> 00:47:35,562
Wi Jeong-sin speaking.

866
00:47:36,729 --> 00:47:37,772
Yes.

867
00:47:39,983 --> 00:47:40,984
Sorry, who's this?

868
00:47:43,069 --> 00:47:44,279
[Hyeon-jun sighs]

869
00:47:45,405 --> 00:47:47,407
[air blasting]

870
00:47:52,954 --> 00:47:54,706
When are you gonna be done with this?

871
00:47:54,789 --> 00:47:56,040
I've only just started.

872
00:47:56,666 --> 00:47:58,293
-Hey, you're in the way, kid.
-Okay.

873
00:48:00,461 --> 00:48:01,796
[sighs]

874
00:48:02,547 --> 00:48:04,716
I won't tell Mom about
the whole acting thing.

875
00:48:04,799 --> 00:48:06,050
But you better go back to school.

876
00:48:06,134 --> 00:48:08,344
Let me try it for one year
before I go back.

877
00:48:08,428 --> 00:48:10,054
I'm telling you, it's not worth it.

878
00:48:10,138 --> 00:48:13,558
I know better than anyone how hard
you've been studying, every day and night.

879
00:48:13,641 --> 00:48:16,561
To give all that up for something
that likely has no future?

880
00:48:17,186 --> 00:48:19,105
I really don't like it. [sighs]

881
00:48:19,897 --> 00:48:21,733
Ugh, just go back after the break.

882
00:48:23,151 --> 00:48:24,152
[clicks tongue]

883
00:48:25,153 --> 00:48:27,822
Okay, I'll give it some thought.
Gimme a couple of days.

884
00:48:28,531 --> 00:48:29,574
[sighs]

885
00:48:31,701 --> 00:48:32,910
Okay.

886
00:48:35,455 --> 00:48:36,664
Oh hey, by the way.

887
00:48:36,748 --> 00:48:38,958
Do you wanna go out again
with that reporter?

888
00:48:39,626 --> 00:48:40,835
She's totally your type.

889
00:48:40,918 --> 00:48:42,545
Smart, intelligent, resourceful.

890
00:48:42,629 --> 00:48:44,422
-[scoffs]
-Looks-wise, too.

891
00:48:44,505 --> 00:48:45,840
She's your type, right?

892
00:48:49,010 --> 00:48:51,679
You know my type?
What are you talking about?

893
00:48:51,763 --> 00:48:54,432
Yeah, right. You think you know my type?

894
00:48:54,932 --> 00:48:56,184
[exclaims]

895
00:48:56,267 --> 00:48:57,268
Are you okay?

896
00:49:03,358 --> 00:49:05,318
MESSAGES

897
00:49:05,401 --> 00:49:07,236
[inhales deeply]

898
00:49:08,905 --> 00:49:10,823
[typing]

899
00:49:18,122 --> 00:49:20,750
[Seon-u] You need to be
more careful, Hyeon-jun.

900
00:49:20,833 --> 00:49:22,210
-Get some rest, okay?
-[groans]

901
00:49:22,293 --> 00:49:23,461
[Hyeon-jun] All right.

902
00:49:26,714 --> 00:49:29,342
[groaning]

903
00:49:29,425 --> 00:49:31,719
-Why is nothing going my way?
-[door closes]

904
00:49:31,803 --> 00:49:33,971
Should I go see a fortune teller?

905
00:49:34,055 --> 00:49:35,056
THE CARD OF DESTINY

906
00:49:35,139 --> 00:49:36,766
"Online tarot card reading"? Hmm.

907
00:49:36,849 --> 00:49:39,185
So it's possible to do that online?

908
00:49:40,395 --> 00:49:41,437
[chuckles]

909
00:49:41,521 --> 00:49:42,563
OK-JI

910
00:49:42,647 --> 00:49:45,858
Hello, I'm Ok-ji,
your personal tarot counselor.

911
00:49:46,359 --> 00:49:49,070
Oh, yeah, uh… [stammers] Hi there. Hello.

912
00:49:49,153 --> 00:49:50,780
Okay, so what do you want to know?

913
00:49:50,863 --> 00:49:53,449
Things have been a little rough recently.

914
00:49:53,533 --> 00:49:56,828
So, um, tell me,
when will things get better?

915
00:49:56,911 --> 00:49:59,872
I think you mean in relationships,
as well as your work, right?

916
00:49:59,956 --> 00:50:00,998
Uh, yeah.

917
00:50:01,082 --> 00:50:03,292
[Ok-ji] Do you see the tarot cards
appearing on the screen?

918
00:50:03,376 --> 00:50:05,795
-Yes.
-Good. Pick nine cards.

919
00:50:09,507 --> 00:50:10,550
[Ok-ji] Hmm.

920
00:50:11,426 --> 00:50:12,677
Do you see that one card?

921
00:50:12,760 --> 00:50:14,887
These men are holding clubs
and they're fighting each other.

922
00:50:14,971 --> 00:50:16,723
This represents what
you're currently going through.

923
00:50:16,806 --> 00:50:18,307
It means war is on.

924
00:50:19,016 --> 00:50:21,018
It's a dog fight,
and there's no end in sight,

925
00:50:21,102 --> 00:50:23,062
whether it's external
or internal, correct?

926
00:50:23,146 --> 00:50:24,564
Yeah, absolutely spot on.

927
00:50:24,647 --> 00:50:26,274
-That's it.
-The second one tells us your future

928
00:50:26,357 --> 00:50:27,525
three months from now.

929
00:50:27,608 --> 00:50:30,611
It tells us you'll experience heartache.
As if swords were piercing your heart,

930
00:50:30,695 --> 00:50:32,697
or you were struck by bullets.
Bang, bang, bang.

931
00:50:32,780 --> 00:50:34,407
Oh, all right.

932
00:50:34,907 --> 00:50:36,284
So what do you think I need to do?

933
00:50:36,367 --> 00:50:39,162
Well, this one, the third one,
is also very important,

934
00:50:39,245 --> 00:50:41,998
and what I see is that you
should actually be more selfish

935
00:50:42,081 --> 00:50:43,666
-than considerate right now.
-[sighs]

936
00:50:43,750 --> 00:50:46,586
Oh, also, do you have
a bad back by any chance?

937
00:50:46,669 --> 00:50:49,088
Oh, yeah. How'd you know that, though?

938
00:50:49,172 --> 00:50:52,925
People who have back problems, um,
they tend to pick the Ten of Swords.

939
00:50:53,009 --> 00:50:56,429
[chuckling] Good Lord! You're so good,
I'm starting to get a little scared.

940
00:50:56,512 --> 00:50:57,638
Don't be scared.

941
00:50:58,848 --> 00:51:01,893
Anyway, so the cards are telling me
that your complicated situation

942
00:51:01,976 --> 00:51:04,729
is unfortunately not quite over yet.

943
00:51:06,189 --> 00:51:07,190
[sighs]

944
00:51:07,982 --> 00:51:10,693
Um, there's just one more question.

945
00:51:10,777 --> 00:51:12,487
The work I'm doing is going really well,

946
00:51:12,570 --> 00:51:14,739
but I really wanna try something else.

947
00:51:14,822 --> 00:51:16,491
I don't think there's room for growth.

948
00:51:16,574 --> 00:51:19,243
Not with what I'm doing now.
I just feel like I'm stuck somewhat.

949
00:51:19,327 --> 00:51:21,996
Stuck and unable to lean in
and move forward.

950
00:51:24,499 --> 00:51:25,583
Should I…

951
00:51:26,959 --> 00:51:30,004
go for it and start something new?

952
00:51:30,713 --> 00:51:33,424
[Ok-ji] Right now, it would be better
to just keep doing what you're doing,

953
00:51:33,508 --> 00:51:35,551
instead of venturing out
too far professionally.

954
00:51:35,635 --> 00:51:38,179
-[scoffs]
-Don't let greed get the better of you.

955
00:51:38,262 --> 00:51:41,265
The cards tell me that if you succeed
in what you're currently doing,

956
00:51:41,349 --> 00:51:43,893
it will lead to better opportunities
down the road.

957
00:51:43,976 --> 00:51:47,396
[sobbing] What do you know?
You don't know anything.

958
00:51:50,983 --> 00:51:52,109
[phone buzzes]

959
00:51:55,404 --> 00:51:57,865
[Soo-jung] Meet me at Rozan Cafe at 8 p.m.

960
00:51:57,949 --> 00:51:59,200
[whispers] 8 p.m., Rozan.

961
00:51:59,283 --> 00:52:00,535
[sighs]

962
00:52:01,661 --> 00:52:03,412
So, you're really not gonna do that movie?

963
00:52:03,496 --> 00:52:04,914
No, I'm not gonna do it!

964
00:52:04,997 --> 00:52:06,499
-Just because Se-na's in it?
-Cut it out!

965
00:52:06,582 --> 00:52:08,292
You gotta do Kang Pil-gu, then.

966
00:52:08,376 --> 00:52:10,336
Do what?
First they've gotta get a director.

967
00:52:11,295 --> 00:52:12,880
Glad you brought it up,

968
00:52:12,964 --> 00:52:15,174
'cause I think we should have
a meeting with the director first.

969
00:52:15,258 --> 00:52:16,300
And which director?

970
00:52:16,384 --> 00:52:17,510
Can't we just meet them?

971
00:52:17,593 --> 00:52:19,846
I know you'll wanna pull out of it
if I tell you who it is.

972
00:52:19,929 --> 00:52:22,014
Let's just have the meeting
and we'll talk after, okay?

973
00:52:22,098 --> 00:52:25,059
God, I'm so stressed out
being caught in the cross fire.

974
00:52:25,142 --> 00:52:26,394
You do this every time.

975
00:52:26,477 --> 00:52:29,313
You always call me here
when you have something to whine about.

976
00:52:29,397 --> 00:52:31,232
[Ji-sun sighs]

977
00:52:32,233 --> 00:52:34,652
Don't let greed get the better of you.

978
00:52:34,735 --> 00:52:37,697
The cards tell me that if you succeed
in what you're currently doing,

979
00:52:37,780 --> 00:52:40,074
it will lead to better opportunities
down the road.

980
00:52:40,658 --> 00:52:43,661
I really wanted to quit this time,
no matter what.

981
00:52:45,496 --> 00:52:46,789
But for your sake I'll do it.

982
00:52:46,873 --> 00:52:49,500
All right, I get it, it's your choice.

983
00:52:50,418 --> 00:52:51,669
Wait, what?

984
00:52:51,752 --> 00:52:53,796
[stammers] You said you're gonna do it?

985
00:52:53,880 --> 00:52:54,964
Yes, I will.

986
00:52:55,047 --> 00:52:56,883
Huh? You're sure, yeah?

987
00:52:56,966 --> 00:52:59,260
I've gotta make a recording of this.
Hang on a second.

988
00:52:59,343 --> 00:53:00,344
I'm recording, yeah?

989
00:53:00,428 --> 00:53:02,763
-Yeah, yeah, yeah. Yeah!
-Yeah? Yeah? Yeah? You said so.

990
00:53:02,847 --> 00:53:04,599
I'll hit the record button, now say it.

991
00:53:04,682 --> 00:53:06,726
You will agree to season five?

992
00:53:06,809 --> 00:53:10,980
I, Lim Hyeon-jun, will agree to do
Kang Pil-gu season five.

993
00:53:11,063 --> 00:53:12,440
No matter what.

994
00:53:12,523 --> 00:53:15,484
Nice! Okay. [laughing]

995
00:53:18,404 --> 00:53:19,447
You're way too excited.

996
00:53:25,161 --> 00:53:26,203
[sighs]

997
00:53:27,413 --> 00:53:29,206
[suspenseful music playing]

998
00:53:36,923 --> 00:53:37,924
[Jeong-sin] Hey.

999
00:53:44,138 --> 00:53:45,306
[sighs]

1000
00:53:47,850 --> 00:53:49,560
[Jeong-sin] Are you Bahn Soo-jung?

1001
00:53:49,644 --> 00:53:51,020
How do you know who I am?

1002
00:53:51,103 --> 00:53:52,939
Thank you for doing this.

1003
00:53:53,022 --> 00:53:55,733
But why did you decide
to get in touch with me?

1004
00:53:56,525 --> 00:53:59,403
You seemed like
the kind of person I could trust.

1005
00:54:00,446 --> 00:54:02,615
[Jeong-sin] I know about
your 12-year-old sibling,

1006
00:54:02,698 --> 00:54:05,242
who's been bedridden
due to a rare illness.

1007
00:54:05,326 --> 00:54:07,453
You should contact this place.

1008
00:54:07,536 --> 00:54:10,122
There's gotta be a way
to take care of them without working here.

1009
00:54:12,458 --> 00:54:16,420
Thanks to you, my sibling
is receiving treatment now.

1010
00:54:16,504 --> 00:54:18,714
-So you've left that job, yeah?
-Yeah.

1011
00:54:19,590 --> 00:54:20,591
Anyway,

1012
00:54:21,467 --> 00:54:22,718
why am I here?

1013
00:54:24,178 --> 00:54:25,179
Uh…

1014
00:54:25,262 --> 00:54:26,806
I know something, which I'm…

1015
00:54:27,598 --> 00:54:29,475
I'm too afraid to keep to myself.

1016
00:54:31,310 --> 00:54:33,521
Remember that video I sent you?

1017
00:54:33,604 --> 00:54:37,233
[manager] Seriously, the script
for the new season is just incredible!

1018
00:54:37,316 --> 00:54:39,735
Mister Bak is
such an amazing writer, isn't he?

1019
00:54:39,819 --> 00:54:41,112
-[chuckles]
-I know. What a twist.

1020
00:54:41,195 --> 00:54:43,531
That the good detective
Kang Pil-gu falls from grace

1021
00:54:43,614 --> 00:54:45,408
and turns into a corrupt cop.

1022
00:54:45,491 --> 00:54:46,909
-So creative, so compelling.
-It truly is.

1023
00:54:46,993 --> 00:54:48,452
Hyeon-jun, I want you to know

1024
00:54:48,536 --> 00:54:52,081
how deeply grateful all of us are
for you making this decisive call.

1025
00:54:52,164 --> 00:54:54,542
Seriously, Hyeon-jun, you did,
you saved us all!

1026
00:54:54,625 --> 00:54:56,919
At his age, who's casting him
in a rom-com or a drama?

1027
00:54:57,003 --> 00:54:59,171
Kang Pil-gu's all he's got.
What else can he do?

1028
00:54:59,255 --> 00:55:02,717
[chuckling]

1029
00:55:02,800 --> 00:55:04,844
[sighs] That's very sweet of you.

1030
00:55:04,927 --> 00:55:05,928
[chuckles]

1031
00:55:06,595 --> 00:55:07,805
But I'm more grateful.

1032
00:55:07,888 --> 00:55:09,932
Oh, no. No! [chuckles]

1033
00:55:11,308 --> 00:55:13,394
So, um, where's the director?

1034
00:55:14,520 --> 00:55:16,063
And also where's Mr. Bak?

1035
00:55:17,523 --> 00:55:20,609
Oh, um… [clears throat]
They're arriving together.

1036
00:55:20,693 --> 00:55:21,736
-Yeah.
-[Ji-sun] Aren't they?

1037
00:55:21,819 --> 00:55:23,821
-Together?
-Mm-hmm.

1038
00:55:23,904 --> 00:55:26,490
Stop! I'm so curious now. Guys, come on.

1039
00:55:26,574 --> 00:55:29,118
Just say it. Tell me who it is already.

1040
00:55:29,201 --> 00:55:30,870
-Mr. Hwang?
-[Byeong-gi] Hello, hello.

1041
00:55:30,953 --> 00:55:32,538
Uh, oh… [chuckles]

1042
00:55:32,621 --> 00:55:34,582
-Come in. Have a seat.
-Evening.

1043
00:55:35,458 --> 00:55:36,876
What about the director?

1044
00:55:36,959 --> 00:55:38,627
Weren't you coming together?

1045
00:55:40,337 --> 00:55:41,964
So I guess you haven't told him?

1046
00:55:42,590 --> 00:55:44,884
Tell me what exactly?

1047
00:55:46,969 --> 00:55:48,763
-[sighs]
-[chuckles]

1048
00:55:48,846 --> 00:55:51,140
What is happening?
Why are you all acting weird suddenly?

1049
00:55:58,189 --> 00:55:59,315
Hmm…

1050
00:56:01,067 --> 00:56:02,276
No, you didn't…

1051
00:56:09,325 --> 00:56:10,993
I don't believe it, hmm?

1052
00:56:13,954 --> 00:56:15,164
This isn't what I think is it?

1053
00:56:15,247 --> 00:56:16,749
Mr. Bak is gonna do it, yes.

1054
00:56:19,376 --> 00:56:20,920
He's doing it? [chuckles]

1055
00:56:21,921 --> 00:56:23,339
Doing what?

1056
00:56:26,467 --> 00:56:27,760
Direct the show.

1057
00:56:28,469 --> 00:56:31,138
[manager] He'll be writing and directing
the new season of Kang Pil-gu.

1058
00:56:31,222 --> 00:56:32,890
It's already decided. It's done.

1059
00:56:38,604 --> 00:56:39,605
[groans]

1060
00:56:40,356 --> 00:56:41,482
You've…

1061
00:56:42,399 --> 00:56:43,526
[wheezes]

1062
00:56:44,819 --> 00:56:45,903
You're directing it?

1063
00:56:45,986 --> 00:56:47,613
[Hyeon-jun groans]

1064
00:56:47,696 --> 00:56:49,240
I will do my best, Hyeon-Jun!

1065
00:56:49,865 --> 00:56:51,742
Yeah, take it. Take your pill now.

1066
00:56:52,451 --> 00:56:54,161
[Byeong-gi, echoing]
Cut. Cut. Let's try that again.

1067
00:56:54,245 --> 00:56:55,246
Cut!

1068
00:56:55,329 --> 00:56:56,747
Ready. Action!

1069
00:56:56,831 --> 00:56:59,250
Cut. Ready. Action!

1070
00:56:59,333 --> 00:57:00,334
[thuds]

1071
00:57:00,417 --> 00:57:02,920
Cut! Don't stop. If I don't call cut,
just let it keep going.

1072
00:57:03,003 --> 00:57:04,046
Just let it play out.

1073
00:57:04,130 --> 00:57:06,966
It seems like you haven't had enough time
to fully analyze your character.

1074
00:57:07,049 --> 00:57:09,343
Let's reshoot the scenes another time.
Don't flatter yourself.

1075
00:57:09,426 --> 00:57:11,637
You've never worked
with Bong Joon-ho or Park Chan-wook.

1076
00:57:11,720 --> 00:57:13,013
Action!

1077
00:57:13,097 --> 00:57:16,308
Honestly, sir, I wouldn't have begged if I
had known you were such a terrible actor.

1078
00:57:16,934 --> 00:57:17,935
One more thing…

1079
00:57:18,018 --> 00:57:22,565
You little bastard! I never wanna see
your freaking face again!

1080
00:58:01,979 --> 00:58:04,732
[Soo-jung] Remember that video I sent you?

1081
00:58:05,357 --> 00:58:08,068
There is somebody
who doesn't appear in the video.

1082
00:58:08,152 --> 00:58:10,154
[tense music playing]

1083
00:58:17,036 --> 00:58:19,330
It's someone very famous.

1084
00:58:27,963 --> 00:58:29,465
Gwon Se-na.

1085
00:58:53,656 --> 00:58:55,741
[no audible dialogue]

1086
00:59:00,037 --> 00:59:02,039
[music continues]

1087
00:59:18,973 --> 00:59:20,766
[theme music playing]

1088
00:59:47,876 --> 00:59:50,129
SPECIAL THANKS TO OH YEON-SEO
FOR HER APPEARANCE

1089
00:59:53,299 --> 00:59:54,717
It's your first time at a stadium, right?

1090
00:59:54,800 --> 00:59:56,927
Let's watch the game together
after the interview.

1091
00:59:57,011 --> 00:59:58,262
Sure.

1092
00:59:58,345 --> 00:59:59,805
How am I supposed
to write a proper article

1093
00:59:59,888 --> 01:00:02,433
if you're only giving me one word answers?

1094
01:00:02,516 --> 01:00:04,226
I'm meeting Ms. Wi. Are you coming?

1095
01:00:04,310 --> 01:00:06,979
The shoot's gonna finish
before six, right?

1096
01:00:07,062 --> 01:00:08,480
-[Gil-su] It's 6 o'clock.
-It's 6 o'clock?

1097
01:00:08,564 --> 01:00:10,190
-[shouts]
-How much further is it?

1098
01:00:10,274 --> 01:00:11,483
When are we gonna be there?

1099
01:00:11,567 --> 01:00:12,693
Can you hurry up a little?

1100
01:00:13,485 --> 01:00:14,945
It's been a while.

1101
01:00:15,029 --> 01:00:16,905
I know another place. It's good.

1102
01:00:16,989 --> 01:00:18,615
It's dark and secluded.

1103
01:00:19,366 --> 01:00:21,201
[Hyeon-jun, echoing] Where, where…
